description_0: A view of cumulus clouds taken from below. The cumulus clouds are very wispy and thin. The right half of the frame has less clouds with large portions of clear sky visible. The sun is hitting the clouds on the right giving them a hint of light. The clouds on the left side don't have sun hitting the majority of them giving them a dark, black look.
description_1: An overhead view of a grass surface with spring cinquefoil flowers spread throughout the entire image. The flowers are small and yellow. There are patches of dry dirt at the bottom right corner and left side of the image. There is a broken off tree limb on the ground in the top right corner of the image. There are sticks scattered on the ground at the top of the image.
